<HEADLINE> China, Japan Ink Large Fluor Chemical Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 14 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan has recently signed
a letter of intent here on the joint development of the country's
largest fluor chemical project.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Daikin Corporation and the China Chemical Construction
Corporation pledged to pour 114 million US dollars into the
construction of a production base in Changshu in east China's
Jiangsu Province. The Japanese and Chinese sides will hold
respectively 80 percent and 20 percent of the shares.
</P>
<P>
China is the world's leader in fluor spar deposits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
