<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Concerned over Reported Clashes in North Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 14 (Xinhua) -- The British government has expressed
its concern over the reported clashes between Turkish troops and
Kurdish forces in northern Iraq and urged Turkish government to
exercise restraint.
</P>
<P>
British foreign office minister Doug Henderson said in a
statement issued this afternoon that the British government was
"concerned that Turkish troops are reported to be advancing over
the border with Northern Iraq in a move against the Kurdistan
Workers' Party."
</P>
<P>
"We support Turkey's aim of maintaining her own territorial
integrity and protecting her legitimate security interests. We are
urging the Turks not to exceed measures necessary to protect these
interests," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Britain understand that "Turkey has no wish to
challenge Iraq's territorial integrity and we do not believe the
problem can be solved by military means alone."
</P>
<P>
"We are also stressing to the Turks the importance of
respecting human rights and of avoiding actions which might
endanger innocent civilians in the region," he added.
</P>
<P>
It was reported the border areas of northern Iraq have been the
scene of fighting between Turkish security forces and Kurdish
armed forces before and some 22,000 people have been killed over
the past 12 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
