<HEADLINE> FIFA World Cup Trophy Worldwide Tour Kicked Off in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 14 (Xinhua) -- The FIFA World Cup trophy was
unveiled here today, kicking off the first-ever world tour of this
coveted prize which represents the game's top honor.
</P>
<P>
The trophy will be on display for three days in the New World
Plaza here, marking the start of the prestigious trophy's
first-ever public appearance in Asia.
</P>
<P>
After Hong Kong, the Budweiser-sponsored FIFA World Cup Trophy
Tour will go to 10 other countries and regions through November,
making stops in countries such as China, Japan, South Korea and
those in Europe and South America.
</P>
<P>
The FIFA World Cup is a 67-year-old tournament held every four
years and is regarded as the ultimate international football event
determining the best team as the "world champion".
</P>
<P>
The 16th World Cup finals will be held in France in the summer
of 1998 while the 2002 World Cup will take place in Asia for the
first time and is to be split, also for the first time, between
joint hosts Japan and South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
