<HEADLINE> Kabila Leaves Angolan Capital for Talks with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 14 (Xinhua) -- Zairean rebel leader Laurent
Kabila left here today for northern Angolan city of Cabinda
from where he will go to a South African Navy ship off the
Congo coast to hold peace talks with Zairean President Mobutu
Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving the airport, Kabila told reporters that during
the forthcoming face-to-face talks, he will ask Mobutu to hand
over power to the rebel Alliance of Democratic Forces for the
Liberation of Congo-Zaire led by him.
</P>
<P>
This will be the second round of talks between the two rivals
of Zaire. On May 4, they held peace talks on the Zaire crisis on
the same ship, the SAS Outeniqua.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Kabila held discussions with Angolan
President Jose Eduardo dos Santos on the Zairean conflict. But he
did not reveal any details of the discussions. enditem


