<HEADLINE> Georgian President Pays First Visit to Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 14 (Xinhua) -- Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze
paid his first visit to Italy today, holding "long and cordial"
talks with Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro.
</P>
<P>
The Georgian embassy said Scalfaro praised Shevardnadze for his
work as the former Soviet foreign minister under President Mikhail
Gorbachev and for his contribution to the founding of the new
independent republic of Georgia after the collapse of the Soviet
Union.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro agreed with Shevardnadze on the need for Italy to set
up diplomatic representation in Georgia as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Shevardnadze also attended a seminar on the Georgian economy
organized by the Italian employers' association Confindustria.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with Italian parliamentary speakers, President
Shevardnadze unveiled a show of religious art by Georgian artist
Irakli Parjiania at the Gregorian University.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow afternoon President Shevardnadze will meet top
officials of the Rome-based United Nations food and agriculture
agencies, as well as the World Food Program.
</P>
<P>
President Shevardnadze's visit is being billed here as the
first by a Georgian head of state to Italy in over 18
centuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
