<HEADLINE> France to Send 40 Tons of Aid Materials to Iran Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 14 (Xinhua) -- France will send a second cargo plane
carrying 40 tons of aid materials to Iran on Thursday to help the
victims of the devastating earthquake which struck eastern Iran
last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The plane, carrying two sets of water purification equipments,
food, covers, clothes, medicines and medical equipments, will fly
to Mashhad, capital of the region devastated by the earthquake,
said Francois Brisset, spokesman of the French Secretariat for
Emergency Humanitarian Action.
</P>
<P>
The first cargo plane carrying aid materials from France
arrived in Mashhad on Sunday. The aid materials were later
transferred to Birjand, a town near the Afghan border, by planes
and helicopters.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Red Cross said that 1,613 people were killed and
3,712 injured in the earthquake.
</P>
<P>
France offered to send a rescue team to Iran to help carry out
rescue operations, but the Iranian government turned down the
offer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
