<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Kill 11 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 14 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed and 27
others injured in two separate traffic accidents in the past 24
hours in India, the Press Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
Three people were killed and 17 others injured when a bus
carrying a marriage party overturned in India's Uttar Pradesh
today.
</P>
<P>
Police said four of the injured were in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Also in Uttar Pradesh, seven people, including two women and
three children, were killed and 10 injured when a bus and a jeep
had a head-on collision on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when the jeep tried to overtake another
vehicle, police said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
