<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Provides Emergency Aid for Iran Earthquake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 14 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, European
Union's executive body, said on Wednesday that it had approved a
package of emergency aid worth ECU three million(3.39 million US
dollars) for victims of last weekend's catastrophic earthquake in
Iran.
</P>
<P>
According to the European Community Humanitarian Office(ECHO)
which manages the aid, the EU will send food aid, tents, clothing,
blankets, drinking water equipment and latrines, as well as
medicines and medical supplies to the stricken area.
</P>
<P>
The International Federation of Red Cross, Red Crescent
Societies and two French non-governmental organizations will take
part in the coordinated aid action.
</P>
<P>
The death toll in Iran's worst earthquake in 20 years is at
present at least 1,560 and some 6,000 people have been injured.
</P>
<P>
The series of quakes, which struck the northeastern province of
Khorosan from 10 May onwards, destroyed at least 150 villages,
leaving some 75,000 people homeless.  
</P>
</TEXT>
