<HEADLINE> EC Clears Telecom Companies BT, MCI Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 14 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
European Union's executive body, said on Wednesday that it had
cleared the pound 12 billion planned merger between British
Telecom and the MCI Communications Corporation of the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The Commission said that the proposed merger would have created
or reinforced a dominant position in the markets for international
voice telephony service on the UK-US route and for
audio-conferencing services in the UK.
</P>
<P>
"However, the Commission has considered that the undertakings
proposed by the parties during the proceedings are sufficient to
address the competition concerns... and compatible with EU's
common market," it was stated in a Commission statement.
</P>
<P>
This merger deal will create the wourld's fourth largest
telephone company and is one of the biggest in UK corporate
history. But the merger still has to be cleared by American
regulators.  
