role as the peace facilitator, ruling out reports that there were
covert plans to kill the former Tanzanian president on grounds
that he was impeding peace in Burundi.
</P>
<P>
During the two-hour talks with Nyerere at the latter's Msasani
residence, Buyoya also sought clarification on the common list of
items which qualify to enter Burundi under the April decision to
ease trade sanctions imposed by African countries on Burundi.
</P>
<P>
Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda, Rwanda and Zaire slapped a trade
embargo on Burundi's military government last year, opposing a
military coup which deposed former President Sylvestre
Ntibatunganya. 
