<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Big Loans for China, Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 14 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of two big loans for China and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The Bank will provide a 120 million U.S. dollar loan for
China's Heilongjiang Agricultural Development Project. The project
is aimed to raise rural incomes and living standards, stimulate
market-oriented enterprise development in rural industries of the
Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
It will also help expand rural employment by increasing
livestock and aquaculture production and expanding or improving
crop and livestock processing.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of some 143.4 million dollars equivalent is
earmarked for Thailand's Universities Science and Engineering
Education Project.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to improve the quality of undergraduate
science and engineering programs in 21 public universities by
strengthening teaching programs, upgrading the curriculum and
broadening the range of science and engineering programs,
modernizing laboratories and improving management.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the World Bank also approved a loan equivalent to
some 26.5 million U.S. dollars for Tunisia's Natural Resources
Management Project. The project will promote sustainable natural
resources management by improving management practices, preserving
resources, improving rural communities' standard of living.
</P>
