<HEADLINE> China, France Sign Agreements, Contracts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- A package of agreements and an
exchange of notes were signed here today between the Chinese and
French governments.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and visiting French President
Jacques Chirac were present at today's signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
They included an exchange of notes on retaining the French
consulate-general in Hong Kong, an agreement on cooperation for
environmental protection, an agreement on cooperation for
developing the peaceful use of nuclear power, a cooperation accord
on health care and medical science, an agreement on cooperation in
research and the peaceful use of outer space, and an agreement on
the quarantine and hygiene of frozen semen of cows, fowls and eggs
for breeding purposes, pigs and horses imported from France by
China.
</P>
<P>
Other documents signed included a framework agreement on an
order by the China Aviation Suppliers' Import and Export
Corporation for 30 Airbuses, and a cooperation accord on the joint
manufacture of the 100-seater civil-use jet planes.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon, economic representatives of the two countries
signed six economic and trading contracts and agreements,
including a contract for Xinjiang Airlines' purchase of 10 ATR-72
planes, an accord of cooperation on the manufacture of 5.5-ton
helicopter wings, a letter of intent on a Sino-French venture for
fasteners for use in aircraft, an agreement on a joint venture for
plant protection, and an agreement of cooperation on aviation
propulsion facilities. 
</P>
