The 20th Hong Kong Footballers Award and the 12th Youth
Footballers Award is jointly organized by Radio 1 of Radio
Television Hong Kong, the Hong Kong Football Association and Hong
Kong Chinese Footballers' Association.
</P>
<P>
Eleven outstanding football players in this year's competitions
and two younger players under the age of 23 will be nominated
through voting by sports editors and reporters from the local
media and by leaders and coaches of Hong Kong's first division
teams.
</P>
<P>
In the past, only Chinese players were eligible for such
selection. But this year's criteria has been changed so that
players of any nationality are now equally eligible.
</P>
<P>
But players who have been given the marching order twice this
season will be the exception.
</P>
<P>
And this year's Footballer of the Year will finally be picked
up from the 11 nominees in June this year. 
