<HEADLINE> Method of Forming Legislative Council of HKSAR Discussed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The panel for the Method of
Formation of the First Legislative Council of the Preparatory
Committee for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
held its third session here from May 14 to 15.
</P>
<P>
The panel discussed a document drafted by the Secretariat of
the Preparatory Committee on the specific method for forming the
first Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
The committee members aired their opinions on the qualification
of candidates for membership of the first legislature and
geographical constituencies through direct elections by taking the
methods of multiple seats with a single vote or seat allocation
according to proportion.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the allocation of 30 seats by functional
constituencies, the composition of the Election Committee and how
to carry out the stipulation that the number of the permanent Hong
Kong SAR residents of non-Chinese nationality or permanent
Hong Kong SAR residents who have the right of abode in foreign
countries will not surpass 20 percent of the total members of the
first Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
The results of discussion will be submitted to the meeting of
the Preparatory Committee to be held here at the end of this month
for making a decision after further discussions.  
</P>
