<HEADLINE> Austrian Skier Banned for Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian Ski Federation banned
Andreas Goldberger for six months for using cocaine on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Goldberger, twice a winner of ski jumping's overall World Cup,
was banned from April 21 untie October 20.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian federation made the decision at a meeting in
Kitzbuehel, according to the federation's spokesman Josef Schmidt.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Goldberger admitted on television he had tried
cocaine once at a Vienna disco but dismissed accusations of having
bought, sold and regularly consumed the drug.
</P>
<P>
Goldberger is very popular in Austria and was voted the
country's 1996 sportsman of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
