<HEADLINE> Tung: HK People Able to Build Better Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The people of Hong Kong are
ready, willing and immensely capable of building an even better
life for themselves as members of the SAR of the People's Republic
 of China, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa said today.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a keynote speech at the Asia Society Annual Dinner
here this evening, Tung said many recent surveys have shown that
the people of Hong Kong are confident that the HKSAR government
will succeed.
</P>
<P>
"The confidence, which stands at 80 percent, is at an all-time
high and is certainly reflected in our booming stock market and
real estate market," he said.
</P>
<P>
Refuting the perception that confidence in Hong Kong has
completely eroded and that Hong Kong will cease to be a commercial
hub in Asia, Tung said the reality is that the Heritage Foundation
rated Hong Kong as the freest economy in the world while the World
Economic Forum regards Hong Kong as the second most attractive
international economy.
</P>
<P>
"Despite 12 years' advance notice of the handover, Hong Kong
continues to be the regional headquarters to more than 700 major
multinational corporations and 85 of the top 100 international
banks," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the HKSAR will absolutely be able to retain a
high degree of autonomy and the leadership of the country is very
much committed to the "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong" principle.
</P>
<P>
"In the five months since I assumed this responsibility, my
confidence level, in this respect, is higher as each day goes by,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He said all the success factors of Hong Kong will be maintained
and strengthened by the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that I will take on the responsibility for the
coming five years successfully," he declared.  
</P>
</TEXT>
