<HEADLINE> EC Proposes Export Tax on Cereals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC) has
approved a proposal to introduce a tax on the export of certain
cereals and cereal products in order to stabilise wheat prices, it
was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
The level of the tax which can be adjusted in future in the
light of market developments is set at(in ECU/tonne): durum
wheat:10.00; common wheat: 15.00; durum wheat flour:15.00; common
wheat flour: 20.00; durum wheat semolina: 15.00; common wheat
semolina: 20.00. One ECU equals about 1.13 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In recent weeks, wheat prices have been increasing due to a
generally low level of world stocks and uncertainty in regard to
the outlook for this year's harvest both within and outside the EU
as a result of climatic influence.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on this decision, EU Agriculture Commissioner Franz
Fischler said that the introduction of this tax was "merely a
precautionary measure to avoid an overheating of the EU cereals
market". 
</P>
</TEXT>
