<HEADLINE> Chinese, French Presidents Hold Talks (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Both presidents agreed that in the current situation when the
world is moving toward multi-polarization, China and France
should step up consultation and co-operation in international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
The UN is playing an increasingly important role in the
handling of international and regional affairs, and China and
France, both being permanent members of the UN Security Council,
should further their links and coordinate their positions on the
promotion of the reform of the UN, promotion of disarmament,
crackdown on international terrorism, increasing aid for
development, support for multilateral trade and maintenance of
diversity of the world.
</P>
<P>
On the present world situation, Chirac said the two-polar world
no longer exists, and a multi-polarized world is now taking shape
worldwide. France and China should promote the harmonious
emergence and formation of such a world. Therefore, it is
necessary increase relations between France and China and between
Europe and China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang agreed with Chirac on this, and pointed out that over the
past year or so the world has quickened the pace of
multi-polarization, which has become a prominent characteristic of
the development of the current world situation.
</P>
<P>
China has always attached great importance to France's status
in and influence on international affairs, Jiang said, adding that
especially since Chirac took office, France has persisted in
pursuing an independent foreign policy and played a unique role in
many aspects.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reiterated that at this crucial moment prior to the turn
of the century and the transition in the world pattern, state
leaders of both China and France as well as statesmen of all
countries should take a wider-ranging view, follow the trend of
history and shoulder their historical responsibilities. This way
they can make concerted efforts to establish a just and rational
interantional political and economic order in the next century,
and make the 21st century a new century that will bring prosperity
and stability to all countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen, Chinese vice-premier and foreign minister, Wang
Zhongyu, head of the Chinese Government Reception Committee and
minister in charge of the State Economic and Trade Commission,
Herve De Charette, French foreign minister, and other senior
Chinese and French officials attended the welcoming ceremony and
the talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
