<HEADLINE> Usage of Beira Port Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe continues to be largest user
of the Mozambican eastern port of Beira, with exports in 1996 making
up 76 percent of the total shipments that passed through the port,
the Zimbabwe News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the Beira Corridor Group (BCG),
Zimbabwean exports in the period under review reached 451,800 tonnes,
compared to 282,800 tonnes in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Imports by Zimbabwe excluding fuel in the same period included
242,700 tonnes of wheat, 99,700 tonnes of fertiliser and 58,400
tonnes of maize.
</P>
<P>
Fuel imports totalled 919,399 tonnes, slightly lower compared to
986,400 tonnes in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Besides Zimbabwe, Zambia and Malawi were some of the countries
that used the route most in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, traffic through this route to the sea was expected to
get a boost this year from increased economic ties between the
country and its neighbour Mozambique. enditem

