<HEADLINE> All Set for Southern African Economic Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Eight regional presidents and prime
ministers have so far confirmed they will represent their countries
at a high level networking and intensive discussions on regional
integration at the Southern African Economic Summit to be held in
Harare from May 21 to 23.
</P>
<P>
About 600 regional and international businessmen and experts are
expected to attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the World Economic Forum (WEF) today said
international and regional business communities were showing
increased confidence in the region's potential, with record increased
participation for the summit.
</P>
<P>
Discussions will focus on regional integration, trade,
infrastructure development, improving the region's competitiveness
and privatisation.
</P>
<P>
This year's growing interest in the summit was proof the
international business community was warming to opportunities
existing in southern Africa, said Frederic Sicre, a member of the
Executive Board of WEF. enditem


