<HEADLINE> HK Fashion Week Spring/Summer '97 to Be Held in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- International buyers and
exhibitors will converge here in July to explore the latest
fashion trends and market intelligence at the Hong Kong Fashion
Week Spring/Summer '97, the region's largest fashion trade fair.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC), the
fair between July 16 and 19 will gather more than 350 exhibitors
from 27 countries and regions, all under one roof to display a
wide array of upbeat products ranging from fashion garments to
accessories and trade-related services.
</P>
<P>
European Selection, the platform for the presentation of the
latest designs from Europe, will take part in the fashion week for
the fourth consecutive time, according to a TDC news release
today.
</P>
<P>
Their continuous participation has further enhanced the
importance of Hong Kong as the springboard for European labels to
expand their market in Asia, as well as a reflection of the
growing demand of European fashion in the region, the TDC said.
</P>
<P>
Trendy designs with good-quality workmanship and competitive
pricing from Hong Kong are also being highly sought-after in
recent years. In the coming event, worldwide buyers will be able
to view what Hong Kong, Macao, India, Taiwan and other Asian
exhibitors will offer, further illustrating Asia's strength as a
new force in fashion.
</P>
<P>
To make Hong Kong Fashion Week Spring/Summer '97 a "one-stop
shopping place" for fashion and accessories, the Fashion
Accessories Pavilion will be in the spotlight again this year to
feature up-to-the-minute fashion accessories -- shoes, handbags,
buttons, zippers, scarves and jewelry.
</P>
<P>
The annual Young Fashion Designers' Contest will be staged as
the major highlight of the fashion week for the first time. The
contest will be held at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center Extension on the first night of the four-day fair,
featuring innovative creations from 17 young designers ready to
vie for awards and honors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
