<HEADLINE> Work Starts on Ling Ao Nuclear Power Station (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The construction of a new nuclear
power station in south China's Guangdong Province officially
started today.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng sent a letter of congratulations to the opening
ceremony of the project, and Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo attended
today's ceremony and gave a speech.
</P>
<P>
The Ling Ao Nuclear Power Station (LNPS) is located in Shenzhen
municipality, only some 1.2 km away from the Daya Bay Nuclear
Power Station, which is now in permanent operation.
</P>
<P>
In his letter Premier Li asked all the participants in the
building of the new power station to draw on the successful
experience of the construction of the Daya Bay plant and stick to
the principle of "safety first, quality first."
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu unveiled the foundation stone for the plant and
said that the development of nuclear power is an important part of
China's bid to increase its power resources.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the construction of the Ling Ao station is one of
the key projects listed in the nation's Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000)
</P>
</TEXT>
