<HEADLINE> Filmart '97 Provides Opportunity for TV Productions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's leading television
broadcasting companies will participate in the upcoming Filmart
'97 here in a bid to promote their new products and increase
company exposure, said the Hong Kong Trade Development Council,
organizer of the fair.
</P>
<P>
The event is slated for June 11 to 13 at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The idea behind the yearly market is to promote Hong Kong and
Chinese-language films and consolidate Hong Kong's position as a
regional hub for those seeking to do business in Asia and China.
</P>
<P>
Amen Ng, head of the marketing and sponsorship unit at the
Radio Television Hong Kong, said her company has produced a lot of
popular programs which will be exhibited at the show.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Telecom IMS Managing Director William Lo said his
company will at the fair introduce its innovative product
Interactive TV, a first-ever launch device designed to provide an
integrated home video, music, shopping and banking services, which
the company claims will open a new era for home living.
</P>
<P>
Apart from local participants, some overseas TV organizations
are also interested in the fair. The spokesman of France's FASHION
TV, one of the many overseas exhibitors, said they would like to
meet cable TV and satellite broadcasting operators and promote
their new channel in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to attract thousands of visitors from
around the world. In the TV broadcasting industry, there will be
representatives from China, Singapore and Sweden.
</P>
<P>
As a major regional broadcasting hub, Hong Kong provides
facilities for 10 satellite broadcasters to uplink their signals
to Asia. Hong Kong's viewers have access up to 38 domestic and
regional television channels in a variety of languages.  
</P>
</TEXT>
