<HEADLINE> Work Starts on Ling Ao Nuclear Power Station (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"In the construction of the Ling Ao plant we should abide by
the principle of self-reliance," said the vice-premier, "to better
absorb advanced foreign technologies and propel the development of
China's nuclear power industry."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that proper attention should be paid to safety and
quality together, and all the related departments, including
banks, should coordinate and cooperate with each other so as to
meet the project's schedule.
</P>
<P>
With the total cost estimated at around four billion US
dollars, the Ling Ao project is one of the biggest during the
Ninth Five-Year Plan period in terms of scale and the biggest one
in terms of the use of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Four nuclear power generating units, each of one million kw,
are planned for the station, with two units to be set up in the
first phase of the construction work.
</P>
<P>
The feasibility study for the project was approved in October
1995, and the principal equipment supply contract and loan
agreements were signed in January 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to the overall program of the project, the first two
generating units of the project will be completed and put into
commercial operation in July 2002 and March 2003, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Attending today's ceremony were also officials from the
relevant departments under the State Council, the Guangdong
provincial government and the Shenzhen municipal government,
diplomats from the British and French embassies in China, as well
as representatives from the principal overseas equipment suppliers
and some public figures from Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
