<HEADLINE> Malaysia's First Multimedia Story Book Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia launched its first
multimedia story book today.
</P>
<P>
The book, "Storytime with Arti," is packed in a CD-ROM and
contains four favorite Asian fables in Bahasa Melayu (Malay),
English and Mandarin.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil version of the CD-ROM would be out soon, the
Malaysian national news agency Bernama quoted Managing Director N.
Gunanathan of Articulate Multimedia, the producer of the CD-ROM,
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 20-minute CD-ROM is user-friendly, giving children the
option of having the stories read to them or the freedom of poring
over the stories themselves, Gunanathan said.
</P>
<P>
Besides the stories narrated by Malaysian actress Ramona
Rahman, there are other interesting elements like games, puzzles
and questions which would make every child fully entertained and
educated, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
