<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Identities of Shenzhen Plane Crash Victims Confirmed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The identities of 21 Thai
passengers and one Hong Kong resident killed in a plane crash near
this south China city May 8 have been confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Also confirmed are the identities of four other Thai passengers
injured in the accident.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Notary Office, in accordance with international
practice, notarized examination certificates made out by legal
medical experts and other papers submitted by the city's public
security bureau, and issued death or injury certificates for the
26 crash victims Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The certificates will provide legal evidence for post-accident
procedures.
</P>
<P>
At 9:30 p.m. on May 8, a Boeing 737 jetliner belonging to China
Southern Airlines on route from Chongqing crash landed at Shenzhen
Airport, leaving 35 people dead and three others critically
injured.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the airline will send the four injured
persons and the bodies of the 21 who died back to Thailand
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
