<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Joins Top Three Seeds in Italian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Fourth seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov lost
his third round tie in straight sets to Spaniard Alberto
Berasategui on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Before the match, Kafelnikov was the highest seeded player left
in the Italian Open. The top three seeds Pete Sampras, Michael
Chang and Thomas Muster had all been eliminated in earlier rounds.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, last year's French Open champion, lost the match
6-3, 6-2 in just over an hour.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov has played just five tournaments this season after
breaking his finger in January. He reached the semi-finals in
Hamburg last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
