<HEADLINE> Chinese, French Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
French President Jacques Chirac agreed to build a comprehensive
partnership between the two countries, during official talks here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The presidents exchanged views on major issues that the world
faces today and bilateral relations in a friendly, frank and
intensive way.
</P>
<P>
Jiang extended a warm welcome to Chirac, who arrived here for a
state visit this morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that, as an old friend of the Chinese people and a
statesman, Chirac attaches great importance to the Sino-French
relationship and actively pushes ahead bilateral friendly
cooperation in all fields.
</P>
<P>
"Your visit to China is the first one by a French president for
14 years. It is not only a significant event in bilateral
relations, but also an important event that draws international
attention," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that he is interested not only in China's
historical art and culture, but also more interested in the
present and future of the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that France and the rest of Europe value their
relations with China, because it will have a great impact on the
world's destiny in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations, Jiang said that China has always
treasured its relations with France, and is ready to build a
long-term, stable, friendly and cooperative relationship with
France, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
