<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weightlifting to Make Major Changes From Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The sport of weightlifting may have major
changes from next year, according to the Chinese Weightlifting
Association (CWA) here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Qian Guangjian, Secretary-General of the CWA, said that the 10
categories in the men's and the listed nine divisions in the women's
weightlifting will be deducted to eight and seven respectively.
</P>
<P>
"This change is to be in line with the inclusion of women's
weightlifting at the 2,000 Olympic Games in Sydney," he said.
</P>
<P>
In Sydney in 2,000, women lifters will make their debut in Olympic
history when four divisions of women's weightlifting are included in
the official sports programme.
</P>
<P>
With the inclusion of women's weightlifting in Sydney, the 10
categories in men's section should be deducted to eight on the Olympic
arena.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the plan will be discussed in the congress of the
International Weightlifting Federation (IWF) later this month. "If the
plan is approved in the congress, it will take effect from January 1,
1998," he added.
</P>
<P>
In the year 1993, the IWF made a thorough change of the ten
categories in men's weightlifting, aiming to clean the name of the
sport, which was smeared by doping scandals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
