<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Calls for Development of Cooperative Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng urged here
today that the supply and marketing cooperatives be run better to
further develop the rural economy and help farmers achieve common
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The supply and marketing cooperatives, set up in the 1950s,
are collectively-owned trading agencies for China's
farmers. Nearly 200 million households in rural areas are
connected with the system.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to a national meeting on the work, Li said that the
cooperatives have been playing an even more important role in
serving the agricultural sector, the rural areas and the
farmers.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hoped that cadres and workers in the system
would continue to exchange ideas and turn it into a real
cooperative economic organization belonging to and run by the
farmers themselves, thereby further developing the rural economy
and realizing common prosperity in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Chen Junsheng commended some outstanding
workers in the system. He said that they are model workers who
have been voluntarily providing services for the farmers, and
their selfless spirit should be encouraged throughout the whole of
society.
</P>
<P>
He urged that the reform of the grass-roots cooperatives be
stepped up by improving management and services, and by carrying out
political education among both the cadres and workers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
