<HEADLINE> Tung Welcomes Japanese Decision on HKSAR Passport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), today
expressed welcome to the Japanese government's decision to grant
HKSAR passport holders the same access as holders of BN(O)
documents.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the Japanese government's decision to recognize
HKSAR passports in the same light as BN(O) after July 1 is most
welcome.
</P>
<P>
He said, "The Japanese government is indicating its continued
confidence in Hong Kong. Japanese citizens are invited to keep
visiting Hong Kong and enjoying its attractions as a major
international business, financial and tourism center."
</P>
<P>
He said that Japan joins a lengthening list of countries that
have made this positive decision, adding that he believes
countries that have not yet decided on the issue will recognize
the sound thinking that underlies this decision and follow suit.
</P>
</TEXT>
