<HEADLINE> HK Welcomes Japan's Position on SAR Passport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Hong Kong
government today welcomed the Japanese government's announcement
that Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) passport
holders will be given the same treatment as BN(O) passport
holders.
</P>
<P>
"The treatment of BN (O) and SAR passport holders is generous
in Japanese terms, reflecting the distinctive standing of the SAR
passport," he said. "It signifies the strong and welcome
commitment of the Japanese government to Hong Kong's continued
success."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman reiterated that Japanese citizens are welcome to
visit Hong Kong. "Current arrangements are that they may do so
without a visa for visits of up to one month.
</P>
<P>
"We intend to maintain the current practice. This is in line
with our overall liberal visa policy and is beneficial to Hong
Kong's status as an international trading, financial and tourist
center," the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
