<HEADLINE> Dollar Plunges to 115 Yen Level in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar plunged to the 115
yen level at one point today, hitting a low of 115.60 yen, a level
not seen since January 8.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. currency was changing hands at 116.20-22 yen at 5
p.m., down from 117.15-18 yen at 9 a.m. and from 117.15-25 yen
late Wednesday in New York.
</P>
<P>
Japanese institutional investors moved to sell the dollar at
once, after seeing it tumble overnight in New York, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
On the stock exchange, share prices dropped. The Nikkei average
of 225 selected stocks on the First Section closed at 20,056.31,
down 153.41 points or 0.76 percent, from the previous day's end.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all issues on the
First Section, fell 13.13 points or 0.87 percent to 1,489.18.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section slightly increased to an estimated
430 million shares from Wednesday's 421.15 million shares. 
</P>
