<HEADLINE> Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 15 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have been killed or
injured during the new operation launched by Sri Lankan government
troops Tuesday, according to military sources this evening.
</P>
<P>
The sources said transmission and ground troops confirmed that
more than 100 rebels killed or wounded during the "Jaya Sikuru"
(certain victory) operation.
</P>
<P>
However, they said 18 government troops were also killed and 31
 wounded.
</P>
<P>
This operation, conducted with air force support, is aimed at
securing a safe land route from the Vavuniya area to the
Kilinochchi region.
</P>
<P>
The troops engaged in the operation are continuing their
advance into rebel-held territory, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 14-year-old guerrilla war
for a separate state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
