<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian Meteorological
Department today issued a warning that thunderstorms are expected
to continue in the next two days over the northern part of the
Straits of Melaka (Malacca) due to a low pressure system over the
Andaman Sea.
</P>
<P>
The department said in a statement here that the bad weather
condition will cause winds up to 70 kilometers per hour in the
straits waters.
</P>
<P>
