<HEADLINE> Italy's Industrial Output Down 4.3 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Industrial output in Italy fell 3.6
percent in March, taking the index for the first quarter of 1997
down 4.3 percent over the same period last year, the country's
statistics bureau Istat reported today.
</P>
<P>
March's fall was the fifth in a row since a slight rise of 0.3
percent in October, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The sharpest fall was seen in investment goods, such as
machinery and equipment, down 8.9 percent, followed by
intermediate goods, down 3.3 percent, and consumer goods, down 1.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
By sector, the sharpest falls were seen in machines and
mechanical equipment (-8.9 percent), electrical machines and
electrical and optical equipment (-7.7 percent), non-metal-bearing
mineral processing (-7.6 percent) and the production of metals and
metal products (-7.4 percent).
</P>
<P>
But increases were seen in paper and publishing, up 5.9
percent, and chemicals and synthetic fibres, up 1.7 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
