<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Communist Party Official Meets With Ghanaians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a Standing Committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee, met with a delegation from the National
Democratic Congress (NDC) of Ghana here today, led by Kofi Attor,
deputy general-secretary of the NDC.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that the CPC and the Chinese government pay close
attention to the traditional friendship between China and Ghana
and bilateral co-operation in all areas.
</P>
<P>
Establishing contacts between the CPC and the NDC in accordance
with the four principles of party-to-party relations, he said,
will help deepen mutual understandings, expand co-operation, and
accelerate all-round development of Sino-Ghanaian ties.
</P>
<P>
Hu expressed his thanks for Ghana's consistent "one China"
stand, and its support for China in world affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said he greatly appreciates the important role played by the
NDC in the political life of Ghana. He wished the Ghanaian people
greater achievements in their national construction under
the leadership of president Jerry Rawlings.
</P>
<P>
Although Ghana and China are far from each other, Attor said,
the long-term and vigorous friendship between the two countries
has connected them closely.
</P>
<P>
The NDC pays close attention to China's achievements and
experience in its development, he said, and that the NDC is
willing to increase its friendly contacts with the CPC to further
promote the development of all-round friendly co-operative
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived in Beijing on May 8 as guests of the
CPC. 
</P>
