<HEADLINE> 3 HK Universities Ranked Among Asia's Top 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Three universities in Hong Kong
have been chosen among the best 10 institutions in Asia, a local
newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong University, which trains most of the territory's
civil servants, was ranked third, according to English-language
South China Morning Post. Founded in 1911, Hong Kong University is
the oldest university in the territory.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese University of Hong Kong, singled out for its large
campus and strong commitment to Chinese culture, was fourth and
the Hong Kong University of Science and Technology won the 10th
place for its good facilities.
</P>
<P>
The rating of universities was conducted by Asiaweek magazine
and is to appear in the magazine's May 16 issue. Factors governing
an institution's placing included academic reputation, faculty
resources, student selection, value for money, student-to-teacher
ratio, and average teacher pay and benefits.
</P>
<P>
University of Tokyo and Kyoto University, both in Japan, were
first and second. Peking University on the Chinese mainland ranked
seventh.  
</P>
</TEXT>
