<HEADLINE> Bills on District Organizations Published in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive's Office of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) today
published three bills on the establishment of the provisional
urban council, the provisional regional council and 18 provisional
district boards.
</P>
<P>
"The bills stipulate that members of these provisional district
organizations will be appointed by the Chief Executive and that
the membership should in general be increased by 25 percent," a
spokesman for the office said.
</P>
<P>
"The bills provide for a seamless transition by preserving the
standing orders, rules of procedures, delegations and appointments
made by the existing municipal councils and district boards, and
by assigning the rights, duties, obligations and liabilities of
the existing Urban Council, Regional Council and District Boards
to the Provisional Urban Council, the Provisional Regional Council
and Provisional District Boards, respectively."
</P>
<P>
"At the same time, the bills enable these new district
organizations to benefit from further professional input through
the appointment of additional members," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Urban Council (Amendment) Bill 1997, the Regional Council
(Amendment) Bill 1997 and the District Boards (Amendment) Bill
1997 will be submitted to the Provisional Legislative Council
(PLC) Saturday for first and second readings.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the bills will receive favorable consideration by
the PLC," the spokesman said. "Subject to the passage of the
bills, the Chief Executive will announce the appointments by the
end of May or early June."  
</P>
</TEXT>
