<HEADLINE> Chinese Ferry-Boat Collision Leaves 7 People Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, May 15 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese ferry ship, "Lubodu No.2",
sank Tuesday afternoon when it collided with a Singaporean ship off
the coast of Dalian City in Liaoning Province in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Seven people were reported missing in the collision, which
occurred at about 4:30. According to the Dalian Maritime
Supervision Bureau, the mishap occurred at about 38"31' N latitude
and 121"01' E longitude.
</P>
<P>
The "Lubodu 2" of 960 DWT, which belonged to the Shandong Ocean
Shipping Corporation, was carrying 44 passengers, 29 crew members,
and 15 automobiles.
</P>
<P>
The 174-m-long Singaporean-registered vessel is a container
ship with a gross weight of 16,332 tons. It was loaded with 159
TEUs, and was sailing from Dayaowan Port of Dalian to the Tianjin
New Harbor.
</P>
<P>
Four Chinese naval vessels, two fishing boats, and another
ferry-boat "Lubodu No.1" went to the scene of the accident to
rescue the victims.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the mishap and losses are still under
investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
