<HEADLINE> French International Goal-keeper Banned for Five Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Bernard Lama, goal-keeper of French
natinal team and Paris St Germain, was banned from soccer for five
months on Thursday after failing a drug test.
</P>
<P>
The French Football Federation also annnounced that three of
the five months ban would be suspended.
</P>
<P>
Lama had tested positive for cannabis last February. He took
part in the European Cup Winners Cup final on Wednesday. Paris St
Germain lost the match 1-0 to Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
The ban means that Lama will miss next month's four-nation
tournament which involves Brazil, England, Italy and France.
</P>
