<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Kinkel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice-Premier Zou
Jiahua and German Vice-Chancellor and Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel agreed in their talks here today to further promote
economic, trade and technological cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Zou, who arrived in Germany on Tuesday on a three-day working
visit, said in the talks today that China laid great emphasis on
developing the friendly and cooperative relations with Germany.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Germany were supplementary in conducting
economic and technological cooperation which still had great
potential to tap.
</P>
<P>
Zou expressed the hope that the two countries would make common
efforts to further promote cooperation in all fields and to
develop long-term, stable, and overall friendly and cooperative
relations into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel meanwhile stressed that China is a very important
country, saying that Germany is willing to develop relations with
China in all fields and to explore new cooperative opportunities,
particularly in areas of high technologies and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Zou is on the last leg of his European visit which has also taken
him to Switzerland, France and Norway.
</P>
<P>
Before coming to Bonn, he visited enterprises in Munich and
Nuremburg and will also visit some in Duesseldorf and Berlin
before leaving for Beijing on Friday. 
