<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- President Jacques Chirac today began a four-day state visit in
China in a highly friendly atmosphere between the two countries. The
president, who loves Chinese history and culture, will not have time
to visit historical sites this time and will only engage in
activities for economic purposes, such as opening the Shanghai
exhibition of high-technology products of France.
</P>
<P>
-- After devoting the primary days after his election to European
affairs, British Prime Minister Tony Blair Wednesday presented to
Queen Elizabeth II his government program for the next 18 months
which, as he himself put it, is a ``mixture of realism and
idealism.''
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
