elections in France, President Jacques Chirac asked his government
members not to answer ``provocations'' from the Socialist Party,
which is preparing to launch a counter-offensive against the ruling
majority parties.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure for China, President Chirac urged the ruling
majority to ``avoid dispute'' among themselves and to ``continue to
develop their proposals, their convictions and their vision for the
future.''
</P>
<P>
-- Russian President Boris Yeltsin and all the leaders of the
member countries of NATO will be in Paris on May 27 to sign a
``founding act'' on the new relations between NATO and Russia.
</P>
<P>
After four months of marathon negotiations, Russia and NATO
reached on Wednesday in Moscow an agreement on a document specifying
their future relations. 
