<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader to Visit European Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), will travel to Portugal, Greece and Germany
from May 26 to June 11 on an official goodwill visit, Foreign
Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang announced at a press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit by the chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee to the three countries, Shen said. China has maintained
sound relations with them and there have been frequent contacts in
politics, with co-operation in the economy, economic relations and
trade, science and technology, and culture.
</P>
<P>
Although China and the three nations have different social
systems and varying cultural traditions, Shen added, they all
share the extensive, common interests in maintaining world peace
and promoting economic development.
</P>
<P>
