<HEADLINE> Yu Sets World Weightlifting Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Yu Wenyu of China set a new world
weightlifting record in the women's 70-kilogram snatch at the East
Asian Games here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth weightlifting world record to be broken by
Chinese lifters at the East Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Yu snatched 103 kilograms at her second attempt
to break the world record of 102.5 kilograms held by her
compatriot Tang Weifang. The previous record was set at the Asian
Championships in Yachiyo, Japan, on July 4 last year. 
