<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party's Fine Style of Hard Work, Thrift Urged to Carry Forward (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang Zemin called for greater efforts to look into and deal
with malfeasance by Party officials.
</P>
<P>
Both central and local discipline inspection departments, along
with the active support and participation of the masses, he said,
have intensified efforts to fight against corruption, improve
Party conduct, and build a clean government.
</P>
<P>
"However, it must be seen that to fight against corruption, to
improve the Party's work style, and to build clean government must
be carried out through the entire process of the reform, opening-up,
and modernization drive," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the current situation of struggle against
corruption remains stark, the task to correct the Party's work
style remains arduous, and some negative and corrupt phenomena
have revived and even spread after being cracked down.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that some officials failed to give due attention
to such work, moving slowly on major cases, being slack in
correcting the misconducts in certain departments and trades, or
falling into formalism.
</P>
<P>
Greater determination and efforts and more down-to-earth work
should be done so as to make leading officials become clean and
self-disciplined, to investigate into and deal with lawbreaking
cases, and to correct the misconducts in some departments and
trades, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970515.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party's Fine Style of Hard Work, Thrift Urged to Carry Forward (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In particular, law-breaking cases in leading Party and
government organs, law-enforcement and judicial departments and
departments in charge of business affairs must be handled firmly,
as well as cases involving officials at the county-level or above.
</P>
<P>
Major cases involving financial matters, securities, real
estate, and land leasing also must be seriously investigated and
handled, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Those cases which have caused great impact across the country
or in localities must be investigated according and thoroughly and
dealt with seriously, no matter whoever are involved, and no
matter what obstructions there may be," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Corrupt phenomena among leading officials should draw greater
attention," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The misconducts of extorting, selling or buying, and cheating
official positions must firmly be halted. Although such
misconducts are not universal, they are hazardous and should be
given high priority, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Historical facts have shown that official corruption and
judicial corruption are the worst, and the key reason for breeding
and fostering other forms of corruption," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called attention to the fact that the fight to combat
corruption is a serious struggle which is related to the future
and fate of the Party and the country.
</P>
<P>
"As to this issue, our stance must be clear-cut, our attitude
must be resolute, the work must be done with perseverance," Jiang
said, adding that if the problem is not be handled properly and
well, the country's reform, opening-up, and modernization drive
will have no firm political guarantee and may go astray, and there
may be the hazard of the Party and country's demise.  
</P>
</TEXT>
