<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Further on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to fall on
the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index declined 28.52 points to close at 2069.74 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 168.14 million units, worth 481.87
million Singapore dollars (about 332.32 million U.S. dollars).
Declines once again overwhelmed advances by 292 to 62, while 270
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Poh Lian was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 24.6 million units. It was followed by MBf Capital
which had 10.39 million of shares traded. MBF Holdings was next
with 7.12 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 reversed the downwards trend and rose 1.3 Singapore
dollars to lead the gainers of the day, finishing at 26.1 dollars.
Venture Warrant 9907 gained 90 cents to end at 3.7 Singapore
dollars, while NBT closed 50 cents higher at 11 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS)
Foreign was the biggest loser of the day as it declined 1.1
Singapore dollars to end at 17.9 dollars. The Overseas Chinese
Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign fell one dollar to close at
17.9 Singapore dollars, while the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH)
Foreign and the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign lost 90 cents
each to finish at 28.5 and 14.6 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
