<HEADLINE> Russian Communist Party Leader Ends Visit to Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Russian Communist Party leader
Gennady Zyuganov and his accompanying delegation left here this
morning, winding up a four-day visit to Syria.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement made before leaving here, Zyuganov
described his visit to Syria as "successful, fruitful, constructive
and enjoyable."
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Syria's ruling Arab Baath Socialist Party signed
a cooperation agreement with the Russian Communist Party which
aimed at deepening cooperation between the two parties through
exchange of visits.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Zyuganov met with Syrian President Hafez
Assad and discussed with him a number of international and
regional issues, especially the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Communist Party leader and his accompanying
delegation arrived in Damascus Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
