<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 22 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 15 (Xinhua) -- At Least 22 Tamil rebels have been
killed and 26 others injured by Sri Lankan government troops in
the north of the country since the "Jaya Sikuru" (certain victory)
operation was launched Tuesday, according to the military
spokesman here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that so far the troops have advanced 14
kilometers into the rebel-held territory and they have met with
heavy resistance from the rebels, killing at least 22 and injuring
26. They lost seven soldiers while 24 were injured.
</P>
<P>
The operation, conducted with air force support, is aimed at
securing a safe land route from Vavuniya area to Kilinochchi
region, he said.
</P>
<P>
The operation continued for the third day today, said the
spokesman adding that the troops expected heavy resistance as they
reached Mankulam area shortly.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year-old guerrilla war
for a separate state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
</TEXT>
