<HEADLINE> Cai Zhenhua Named as Head coach of China's Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Cai Zhenhua, one of the key coaches
in the China table tennis team sweeping all seven titles in
Tainjin and six in England, has been named as the head coach of
the team.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old Cai, who coached Chinese men's team since 1991,
was announced on Thursday to take the post which had been vacant
after former head coach Xu Shaofa went abroad in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Lu Yuanshen, coach of the women's team since 1995, will be
Cai's deputy.
</P>
<P>
Yang Hanxiong, who led the Chinese lifters to claime two gold
medals in the Atlanta Olympics last year as the team duputy, was
also appointed to the head coach of the country's weightlifting
team.  
</P>
