<HEADLINE> Party's Fine Style of Hard Work, Thrift Urged to Carry Forward (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Too much money has been spent on buying cars and communication
equipment. During the Eighth Five-year Plan Period (1991-1995)
government departments and institutions, including some
enterprises, spent far too much money on purchasing sedan cars and
cellular phones. Some of the localities and departments could
hardly afford to pay their employees because of their strained
financial conditions, but their leading officials were all
well-equipped with cellular phones;
</P>
<P>
-- Building luxury office buildings and spending huge sums of
public funds on buying or furnishing leading officials'
residential quarters. Two responsible officials of a city's real
estate trust and investment company spent 2.7 million yuan
(325,000 US dollars) of the company buying houses for themselves,
despite the enterprise's managerial difficulties and the housing
problems of most of their employees. Luxury office buildings of
the city's party committee, people's congress and government are
being built one after another. Why on earth build such luxury
office buildings?
</P>
<P>
-- Commemorative events of every description entail the buying
of large amounts of souvenirs and gifts. Some such meetings are
completely meaningless;
</P>
<P>
- The number of meetings of every description, making no
distinction between the necessary and unnecessary, is
excessive. Most of the meetings are held in scenic resorts or
areas with pleasant climates. Very few meetings are held in the
backward northwestern province of Qinghai, for instance.
</P>
<P>
- An excessive amount of subsidies and allowances of every
description are handed out in violation of rules and stipulations.
</P>
</TEXT>
