<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party's Fine Style of Hard Work, Thrift Urged to Carry Forward (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"There are indeed some serious cases of indulging in luxury and
extravagance in the above-mentioned phenomena," the Chinese
president said. And "luxury wastes" are making inroads or ruining
the country.
</P>
<P>
On this issue, some viewpoints should be made clear, he said,
adding that "it is normal to raise the people's living standards
in the wake of economic development. We do not oppose raising
living standards and the goal of the Communists in their work is
to better people's lives.
</P>
<P>
"What we oppose is excessively-high consumption which do not
comply with the current level of economic development," he
said. "And we oppose the use of public office for private gain,
seeking private gain at public expense and harming others to
benefit oneself.
</P>
<P>
"With a vast population, a weak economic basis, few per-capita
resources and not strong enough comprehensive national strength,
China is still facing a host of difficulties and new problems on
its road of advancement, such as pressures arising from the
superior economic, scientific and technological attainment of the
Western developed nations," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We must work hard and arduously for decades or even longer in
order to achieve socialist modernization and catch up with the
level of the developed countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
"At present, China still has a rural population of 58 million
living in need, and the task of relieving poverty in the rural
areas especially is extremely arduous," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"With quite a number of state-owned enterprises operating at a
loss in production and management, millions of workers nationwide
cannot get their full salaries or get them in time," he said. "And
an increasing number of workers are becoming unemployed.
</P>
<P>
"Facing this situation, our leading organs at all levels and
leading officials and the masses of cadres should all the more
conscientiously adhere to the spirit of hard work and
thrift. There is no reason whatsoever to spend public money of the
country and people wastefully," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang revealed that strict measures will be taken to control the
construction of new office buildings for Party and government
organizations at all levels.
</P>
<P>
"The number of meetings, such as commemorative meetings,
symposiums and press conferences will be reduced to the minimum,"
he said. "And the handing out of gifts and so-called souvenirs is
banned completely and indiscriminately from now on."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
