<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party's Fine Style of Hard Work, Thrift Urged to Carry Forward (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"During China's reform and opening-up drive, we should actively
introduce useful things from the developed Western countries while
avoiding citing decadent things as miraculous ones and taking
deep-rooted ulcers as treasured objects," Jiang Zemin noted.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that "in order to realize our ideals, we should
keep to giving full play to our superiority when learning good
experiences from others."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that a society with a bare substance level does not
mean socialism, and spiritual barrenness is not socialism
either. Socialism not only enables people to enjoy an abundant
material life but also enable them to have an enriched and
colorful cultural life too.
</P>
<P>
A number of Communist Party members and officials, including
some ranking officials, he added, seek for and imitate the
decadent Western life style and abandon themselves to the worship
of money and pleasure-seeking, adding that it is very dangerous to
do so.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said, at present, even in Western countries, some
statesmen and men of insight are deeply concerned about the
unchecked spreading of "Western social diseases" such as
pleasure-seeking, spiritual degeneration and decadence.
</P>
</TEXT>
