<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party's Fine Style of Hard Work, Thrift Urged to Carry Forward (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He also urged ranking officials to adhere to the principles in
appointing to posts only those who have the spirit of hard work
and conscientious devotion to the public.
</P>
<P>
Those who are afraid of hard work, and seek pleasure and
extravagance must not be appointed to important posts, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang added that senior officials are not only required to
maintain discipline themselves, but also urged to make sure that
their spouses, children and staff enforce discipline.
</P>
<P>
The central authorities has adopted appropriate regulations,
Jiang said. He called on the discipline inspection and supervisory
organs to strengthen their supervision and ensure that officials
abide by the regulations and resolutely correct mistakes whenever
they are discovered.
</P>
</TEXT>
