<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria, Turkey in Telecommunications Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has begun talks with Turkey
on the development and expanion of its telecommunications
industry, with joint venture partnership and technical
co-operation topping the agenda.
</P>
<P>
The official New Nigerian reported today that a five-member
Turkish delegation is now in Nigeria for the talks.
</P>
<P>
Receiving the delegation on Tuesday in Abuja, the Nigerian
minister of communications, major-general Tajudeen Olanrewaju
reportedly said that the meeting is "very timely", as the two
countries have signed a memorandom of understanding for
telecommuncations co-operations more than 12 year ago.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for Turkey to assist Nigeria in the
fabrication of telecommunication equipment, as well as in
improving the technical expertise in the industry.
</P>
<P>
The minister expressed the hope that at the end of the talks,
a joint venture agreement would be ready for consideration by
both governments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
