<DOCNO> XIE19970515.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore OKeys Primary Listing of 1st Chinese Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Singapore
(SES) has approved in principle the first primary listing of a
Chinese state enterprise on the mainboard in Singapore, local
newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
The approved listing of the Tianjin Zhong Xin Pharmaceutical
Corporation (TZXP), previously known as Tianjin Traditional
Chinese Medicine, is scheduled to go public here next month,
though details of the offer are not yet known, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming public offer of the TZXP stock, called "S"
shares, will be denominated in U.S. dollars, and its public issue
will be lead-managed by the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS)
and co-managed by the Keppel Bank, the Overseas Chinese Banking
Corporation (OCBC) Bank, Overseas Union Bank (OUB), Tat Lee Bank
and the United Overseas Bank (UOB).
</P>
<P>
The pharmaceutical group was tipped widely to be the first
Chinese firm to launch a primary listing here following the
signing of a memorandum of understanding between the securities
regulatory bodies of China and Singapore in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Monetary Authority of Singapore and the Chinese Securities
Regulatory Commission had agreed to co-operate in the regulation
of securities and futures activities in both countries, paving the
way for Chinese companies to come to Singapore for primary listing.
</P>
<P>
The pharmaceutical group, founded in 1955, is a leading
manufacturer of Chinese traditional medicine with 221 registered
products in China.
</P>
<P>
Sales in China accounted for 93 percent of the group's
turnover, while the remaining seven percent came from exports to
Japan, Hong Kong, Singapore, Malaysia, Europe and America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
