<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Increases Efforts to Measure Rural Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 15 (Xinhua) -- China's rural economy is being
subjected to more intensive scrutiny as more agro-projects are
audited, according to sources at a national meeting in Shanghai
recently.
</P>
<P>
Audits were done on 779,000 projects in agro business last
year, with the value audited reaching 567 billion yuan (about 68.3
billion US dollars), statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The audits discovered 6.73 billion yuan in illegal funds,
helping to confiscate illegal funds of 180 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Song Shuyou, an official with the Ministry of Agriculture, said
that the auditing work is expanding to the agricultural sector
rapidly, adding that there were 140,000 auditors for rural areas
at the end of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
