<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southeast China City Developing Township Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises have become a
big drive for economic development around Fuzhou, capital of
southeast China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The township enterprises surrounding Fuzhou saw their output
value climb from 10 billion yuan in 1992 to nearly 63 billion yuan
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Last year the enterprises contributed nearly 63 percent of the
city's industrial output value and conducted nearly 14 billion
yuan worth of exports.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises have provided jobs for the rural surplus labor,
narrowing the gap between the local urban and rural areas. Nearly
45 percent of net income of local farmers now comes from the
township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In 1991-1995, the local township enterprises committed 220
million yuan to rural undertakings involving education, welfare,
and other public projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970515.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: A New Chapter in Sino-African Friendship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li's official visit started in Zambia and ended in Tanzania,
the two countries connected by the 1,900-kilometer Chinese-built
railway, a world famous milestone of China's selfless aid to
African countries.
</P>
<P>
In past decades, China has provided a great deal of aid to
Africa with no attached political conditions, which has played an
active role in helping the African countries develop their economy.
</P>
<P>
However, China itself is also a developing country. Proceeding
from the economic development in the world, in the Africa
countries and in China, it is not suitable for it to provide
constant free aid to the others.
</P>
<P>
Li has been stressing the need to find a more effective way for
mutually benefit cooperation, to widen the areas for economic
cooperation, to turn the sincere willingness for cooperation into
reality, and to give full play to the supplementary nature of the
Sino-African economies.
</P>
<P>
Africa is abundant in natural resources, Li Peng said, that
could be used to help revitalize its economy.
</P>
<P>
Having passed the most difficult period of time, Africa is now
on the way of economic recovery and has made remarkable
achievement, he added.
</P>
<P>
All pessimistic views on the development of the African economy
are baseless, he said, adding that Africa is a continent full of
hope.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of a Sino-Zambian joint-venture textile
company, Li Peng praised the company for taking a form that is
beneficial to the development of both sides.
</P>
<P>
He proposed to speed up the economic cooperation between China
and the African countries in the form of joint ventures, and
specifically talked about how to do it in the fields of forestry,
power, textiles, pharmaceutical production and mining.
</P>
<P>
Africa is rich in natural resources and manpower while China
has the capacity of investment, technology and managing
experience, he said. China and the African countries could promote
their economic cooperation by making full use of their economic
supplementary feature.
</P>
<P>
These ideas, proved by the success of China's opening up and
reform, are the correct choice under the new circumstances, and
have been warmly received by all the leaders.
</P>
<P>
President of Gabon Albert Bongo said that his country is
willing to expand economic ties with China on the basis of
equality and mutual benefits, and stressed that the Chinese
enterprise are welcome to do business in Gabon.
</P>
<P>
Presidents of Cameroon, Zambia and Tanzania also agreed with
Li's ideas. Expressing his willingness to learn from China's
success, Zambian president Fredirick Chiluba cited an old Chinese
aphorism: Giving one fish is not as good as teaching him how to
fish.
</P>
<P>
Li's trip has achieved great results. Twenty agreements on
various projects between China and the six countries have been
signed. Undoubtedly, furthering economic ties and the traditional
friendship between China and African countries by means of more
active cooperation will be a long lasting Chinese policy.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin visited Africa last May. Only in a year,
Premier Li went to this continent again, bringing once more
the good will and best wishes from the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"If the 20th century is the 'century of liberation' for Africa,
then the 21st century will be Africa's 'century of development.'"
Li said. This is not only the wish from Li, but also from all the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li's trip to Africa will prove to be a mile stone in
the long lasting friendship and cooperation between China and the
African countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
