<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Found With Heroin at Zanzibar Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 15 (Xinhua) -- A Dar es Salaam resident,
Mbwana Salum Hassan, was on Tuesday arrested at Zanzibar Airport,
for allegedly with 25 pellets of heroin weighting 250 grams,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the police in Zanzibar on Wednesday said
the suspect was caught shortly after disembarking from a foreign
plane which landed there from New Delhi via Bombay, Muscat to
Zanzibar.
</P>
<P>
Sources hinted that 25-year-old Hassan arrived in Zanzibar
aboard the Gulf Air plane which lands in Zanzibar thrice in a
week.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the suspect has swallowed the pellets but
ejected them through his stool shortly after arriving at the
airport.
</P>
<P>
The police netted the suspect who was about to catch a flight
to Dar es Salaam, and the suspect will appear before the court
after preliminary investigation, said the statement. 
</P>
