<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Hainan, the island province in the
South China Sea, has been listed by the State Council as one of
the 12 key environmental protection areas during the 1996-2010
period.
</P>
<P>
Other areas on the list include Liaohe, Haihe, and the Pearl
River Delta.
</P>
<P>
As one of China's less polluted areas, Hainan will try to avoid
following the "treatment after pollution" path, one local
government official said.
</P>
<P>
According to a plan recently released by the provincial
government, Hainan will make its industrial layout more rational,
hold the discharge of pollutants to a minimum, maintain high water
quality along 80 percent of its coastline, and take steps to
protect the tropical environment and wild plants. 
