<HEADLINE> Shanghai Ranks First in China in Power Equipment Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
industrial center, ranks first in China in the export of equipment
for large power stations and complete sets of machinery, a
municipal official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Electrical Corporation secured an export value of
630 million US dollars in 1996, up 30 percent from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months of this year, its export value hit 100
million US dollars, an all time high compared with last year's
same period.
</P>
<P>
The corporation exported in March two sets of thermal power
generating units, each with a capacity of 325,000 kw. to Iran.
</P>
<P>
Its Export of 15 major products such as power stations, machine
tools, elevators, and engineering tools yielded a profit of 220
million US dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The export value of 112 foreign-funded firms in this sector
totalled 106 million US dollars last year. Their export in the
first quarter of this year registered a 40-percent rise over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts predicted that development of the 400 high-tech
electrical products will boost the export of electrical goods this
year. 
