<HEADLINE> First Tiered Hydropower Station on Hongshui River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Construction workers have been
working hard day and night and moving quickly with the
construction of Tianshengqiao hydropower station on Hongshui
River, southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The station is the first of the planned ten-tiered hydropower
stations to be built on the Hongshui River that originates from
the Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau and traverses into northwestern part of
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
An engineer in charge of the construction said that they will
build a dam with a height of 178 m and construct a reservoir
bearing a holding capacity of 10.2 billion cu m at the power
station.
</P>
<P>
The station will be installed with generators with a combined
generating capacity of 1.2 million kw and will be able to generate
5.22 billion kw/hours of electricity when completed.
</P>
<P>
So far, workers have completed first-stage work of face plate
concrete pouring, which has laid a solid foundation for Guangxi to
tide over the flood season safely this year and electricity
generation by the first generator next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
