<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Archaeologists have discovered a
well-preserved body of a woman in a tomb from the Ming Dynasty
(1368-1644) in Xinyu City, in east China's Jiangxi Province.
</P>
