<HEADLINE> Six Overseas Banks Deal in Chinese Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Two Japanese banks have been added
to the list of foreign banks doing business in Chinese currency in
Shanghai, bringing the number of overseas banks dealing with yuan
to six.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branches of Sanwa Bank and Daiichi Kangyo Bank
have been certified by the People's Bank of China, the central
bank. Since last December, it has approved nine overseas banks for
the yuan business on a trial basis in Shanghai's Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
The other banks are CitiBank, the Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi
Ltd., the Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corporation, the
Industrial Bank of Japan, Standard Chartered, and the
International Bank of Paris and Shanghai, a joint-venture between
France's Banque Nationale de Paris and the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
On March 27, the Shanghai branches of the Hong Kong and
Shanghai Bank and the Industrial Bank of Japan became the first
two overseas banks to provide loans in Chinese currency. They were
soon followed by CitiBank and the Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi.
</P>
<P>
The other three banks are preparing to get involved in the yuan
business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
