<HEADLINE> 440 Ugandan Children Die of Diarrhoea Weekly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 15 (Xinhua) -- About 440 children die of
diarrhoea every week in Uganda, reported the local daily The New
Vision today.
</P>
<P>
Nathan Kenya-Mugisha, manager of Diarrhoeal Disease Control
Program was quoted as saying, the disease is more rampant at
Uganda's districts bordering with Rwanda, Zaire and Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The major reason for the disease is the people in these
districts cannot have clean water to drink and cook.
</P>
<P>
Nathan said it is difficult to construct pit latrines in these
areas which are near lakeshores and which are rocky.
</P>
<P>
For Kitgum and Gulu, he said, the problem is caused by lack of
water for hundreds of displaced people. He said the children die
mainly due to loss of water in the body.
</P>
<P>
He said drugs had been supplied to all health units in the
country to fight the disease and that workers have been trained
to handle the matter and sensitize people on hygiene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
