<HEADLINE> Further Uganda-Sudan Talks Should be Held: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Rebecca Kadaga, Uganda's state
minister for foreign affairs in charge of regional cooperation,
has reiterated that further talks should be held since "our
conditions have been met", "The New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Release of the 19 girls abducted last October is the condition
for further talks between Uganda and Sudan, the Ugandan official
said here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The 19 girls have been captured by the Lord's Resistance Army
(LRA) in northern Ugandan district of Apac.
</P>
<P>
After the return of the girls, Uganda and Sudan would swap the
captured soldiers, the state minister said.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan army have captured 114 Sudanese soldiers last
month in a border clash, and the Sudanese army, in its turn, have
captured two Ugandan army men collecting information in southern
Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Uganda set conditions for further meeting in supreme talks
between the presidents of both Uganda and Sudan last week in
Eldoret, Kenya. 
</P>
</TEXT>
