<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Chinese Export Manufacturers Get ISO9000 Certificates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, May 15 (Xinhua) --Qinghai Measurement and Cutting Tools
Plant in northwest China has been given a certificate for meeting
ISO9000 quality standards, which is considered as a "passport" for
businesses to compete on international market.
</P>
<P>
The plant is the first export-oriented enterprise that has been
given such a certificate in this remote Chinese province.
</P>
<P>
ISO9000 quality standards were worked out by the International
Standardization Organization (ISO) in 1987 in light of modern
management theories on quality control.
</P>
<P>
The ISO9000 quality standard certificate has now become a
guarantee of good product quality, trustworthiness, and modern
management.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Measurement and Cutting Tools Plant produces 58 kinds
of products in 630 specifications which are selling well in more
than a score of countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The plant has also established cooperative ties with
counterpart manufacturing enterprises in a number of countries. It
turned in 3.3 million yuan of pre-tax profits and earned two
million U.S. dollars (one U.S. dollar equals to 8.3 Chinese yuan)
from exports last year.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Province established a working committee in charge of
export-oriented enterprise quality systems in 1993 which did much
to publicize standards of the ISO quality system.
</P>
<P>
The province, together with Shaanxi and Gansu provinces, and
Ningxia Hui and Xinjiang Uygur autonomous regions, also jointly
founded the "China Northwest Assessment Center for Quality System
of Export Manufacturers" in 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
