<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ample Rainfall Relieves Hebei's Heavy Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- An unprecedented rainfall has
relieved the serious drought in Hebei, a major agricultural
province in north China.
</P>
<P>
According to provincial meteorological departments, moderate
rainfall has battered Hebei on seven occasions since late
February. And some areas have reported record amounts of rainfall.
</P>
<P>
Hebei is one of the country's major suppliers of grain and
cotton. However, the province's agriculture has been plagued with
chronic drought year after year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, a severe flood hit the middle and southern part of
the province. The flood, while devastating in nature, left behind
some good effects for this year -- it provided good moist
conditions for the soil, said Zang Jiansheng, director of the
provincial meteorological bureau.
</P>
<P>
However, some experts worry that the record rainfall this
spring may mean more heavy rainfall in the summer, resulting in
major flooding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
