<HEADLINE> Qinghai Deepens Reform of State-owned Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Reform of state-owned firms in west
China's Qinghai province joins the nationwide drive to resuscitate
the debt-ridden sector.
</P>
<P>
Currently, experiments to establish a modern enterprise system,
with independent and business-oriented management, are in place in
many state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 17 state-owned firms in Qinghai will complete
revamping their management mechanism as the first step to
establish modern enterprise systems.
</P>
<P>
Major measures taken by the provincial authorities to
revitalize its large state-owned firms include establishment of
enterprise groups, shareholding renovation, reorganization of
capital, and issuance of stock bonds to pool funds.
</P>
<P>
Flexible measures, including shareholding, shareholding
cooperatives, mergers, incorporation, sale, rent, and bankruptcy,
have also been adopted to enliven small-sized state-owned
firms. 
</P>
