<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Bans Use of Azodyes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 15 (Xinhua) -- In a significant development to
preserve public health and protect the environment, the Indian
government has banned the use of azodyes in the country, the
Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
The use of azodyes, widely utilized for dyeing by the textile
industry, was banned through a gazette notification issued by the
Ministry of Environment.
</P>
<P>
The ban will come into effect from June 23 next, official
sources said.
</P>
<P>
According to the notification, the 70-odd azodyes specified in
the schedule appended to the notification cause cancer and are
detrimental to human health.
</P>
<P>
The ban will apply to the entire country and include all
substances containing these dyes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
