<HEADLINE> Shanghai Museum Develops Automated System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Museum, with a collection
of 100,000 pieces of ancient cultural relics, has recently
developed an automated system.
</P>
<P>
The system, which has just passed the technological appraisal
by the Science and Technology Commission under the Ministry of
Construction, includes a multi-media display direction,
multi-purpose information network, automatic-control devices of
the building and fire monitoring system, the local source said.
</P>
<P>
In the high-tech museum, visitors can view any exhibits by
simply touching the screen of the computer display.
</P>
<P>
Researchers can search pictures and written materials of the
cultural relics through the complex information network.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the automatic-control devices installed in the
building will adjust humidity and temperature within the cabinets
containing the cultural relics, to give the exhibits better
protection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
