<HEADLINE> Italy to Call Conference on Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 14 (Xinhua) -- Italy plans to call an international
conference on Albania on June 18, Italian Foreign Undersecretary
Piero Fassino told a meeting today.
</P>
<P>
The proposed conference, to take place here 11 days before
Albania's scheduled elections on June 29, will be preceded by a
preparatory session on May 26, Fassino said.
</P>
<P>
The decision to call a conference was announced at a meeting
here of the Multinational Protection Force (MPF) for Albania, in
which neighboring Italy plays a leadership role.
</P>
<P>
It came one day after Albanian President Sali Berisha's
Democratic Party threw the pre-election process into turmoil by
forcing an electoral law through the parliament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The legislation by the Democrat-dominated Albanian parliament
was against the wishes of the tiny Balkan nation's other political
parties, including Premier Bashkim Fino's Socialist Party.
</P>
<P>
It spurred calls from the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) and the United States that Berisha
should reconsider and renew efforts to compromise on the law.
</P>
<P>
Fassino stressed that Fino's national unity government,
grudgingly endorsed by Berisha in March after violence and chaos
gripped the country, was "essential" to restoring normality there.
</P>
<P>
Opposition parties in Albania, who threatened to boycott the
elections as they did during the ballot last year, said today they
would consult with Fino and OSCE envoy Franz Vranitzky to frame a
response. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
