<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Has 666 Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- The number of Chinese cities has
risen to 666, four times as many as those 17 years ago, with the
small and medium-sized cities leading such growth.
</P>
<P>
Among the cities, 75 are large cities, 192 are medium-sized
ones and 399 are small, according to the Mayors' Association
under the Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman from the association said the flourishing Chinese
cities have accelerated China's urbanization which is moving
towards the central and western parts. The development also
conforms with the country's strategy to "bring the scale and
number of large cities under control; promote development of small
and medium-sized one and townships."
</P>
<P>
By now, the number of cities in eastern, central, and western China
respectively accounts for 44 percent, 19 percent, and 37 percent of
the national total.
</P>
<P>
China is expected to have 800 cities by the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970515.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
