<P>
He was sure the Philippines could serve as Panama's bridge to
the ASEAN (Association of South East Asian Nations) Free Trade
Area, which includes Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore,
Thailand and Vietnam as well as the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Ramos and his Panamanian counterpart, Ernesto Perez Balladares,
signed four trade and scientific agreements Wednesday, and a pact
making it unnecessary for diplomats from one country to get visas
to travel to the other.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement, the two presidents agreed on the
importance of putting into practice the principle of open
regionalism.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also praised Panama for the country's efforts in
combating international drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Ramos and his delegation arrived here Tuesday for a two-day
official visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
