<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doctors Providing Home Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- A new concept of family doctors who
treat patients in their homes and neighborhoods has been launched
in some of China's major cities, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
"Doctors and nurses in the country's more than 50,000 medium
and small-sized hospitals should boost community medical services
instead of waiting in the hospitals," said Wang Longde,
vice-minister of Public Health.
</P>
<P>
The scheme has already proved a blessing to people like Beijing
resident Zhou Guangyou, 91. When Zhou is feeling sick, instead of
travelling all the way to a hospital, he phones his community
physician Gong Guangcai.
</P>
<P>
"We have got our own family doctor," Zhou proclaimed excitedly
in a letter to his daughter who lives abroad.
</P>
<P>
Gong is one of a team of doctors at Chaoyangmen Hospital,
Beijing, who are treating 74 families in the neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
As part of the new national community health drive, personal
health records will be set up to help diagnose problems as early
as possible and to initiate preventive measures.
</P>
<P>
Simple medical treatment will be available at people's
homes. Health checks will also be conducted via neighborhood
offices, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
A community medical service regulation will be issued this year
by the Ministry of Public Health to help the service which just
started in Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin, and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the doctors' efforts, people will be encouraged to
be routinely vigilant in their health care rather than only
visiting doctors when they become seriously ill.
</P>
<P>
Health care knowledge can play a vital role in preventing
illnesses, including congenital malformations and obesity.
</P>
</TEXT>
