<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Money Pouring Into Flood Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Two eastern coastal provinces have
increased financial aid to their water conservation projects this
year, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 5.7 billion yuan (868 million US dollars),
provided primarily by local governments in Jiangsu Province, has
been poured into investments in major projects, farmland capital
construction and reinforcement of dykes and dams.
</P>
<P>
Irrigation and flood-control measures will support grain
production and improve Jiangsu's ability to withstand the worst
possible water-related disasters, according to provincial
officials.
</P>
<P>
In past years, the province's government made great efforts to
spend more on water projects, itself providing 670 million yuan
(81 million US dollars), and ordering cities and counties to put 2
percent to 4 percent of their finances into water conservancy
facilities.
</P>
<P>
Irrigation projects at Taihu Lake, Wangyu River, Taipu River
and Huaihe River, are expected to be finished before the
high-water season, between late spring and early summer.
</P>
<P>
Already finished is the transformation of 78,700 hectares of
middle-and low-yield farmland.
</P>
<P>
By the end of March, nearly 900 million cubic meters of earth
and stone had been moved.
</P>
<P>
Cities and counties in Fujian Province have included
flood-control funding in their local budgets, one of several
responses to defend themselves against flood damage.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, six cities and 23 counties had earmarked
12.45 million yuan (1.5 million US dollars) for flood-control.
</P>
<P>
Floods followed by droughts, high winds and tides, befall the
province every year, damaging the province's defences.
</P>
<P>
The damaged facilities could not be repaired in time because
the necessary funding had not been included in local budgets,
although local governments did allocate some money for repairs.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the province will increase its
flood-control fund to 30 million yuan from 6 million yuan in the
past years.
</P>
<P>
With the growth of local economies, fund allocations are
expected to grow accordingly.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
