<HEADLINE> Bulgarian PM Authorized to Form New Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, May 14 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov
today authorized newly appointed Prime Minister Ivan Kostov to
form a new government.
</P>
<P>
Kostov, chairman of the most powerful Union of Democratic
Forces, said he would submit a list of cabinet members and the new
government's work plan for the next four years to the president
next Monday. The parliament is expected to endorsed the new
government on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Some key ministers in charge of economic affairs in the current
caretaker government are expected to stay in the new one, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Kostov's party won 123 in the 240-seat parliament in the April
19 general election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
