<HEADLINE> HK Business Giant Join in Shenyang's Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Cheung Kong (Holdings)
Ltd has promised to invest a total of 400 million yuan in the
construction of 6.4-kilometer-long overpass in this capital of
northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The local government has also invested 370 million yuan in the
project, which is to connect the city's eastern and the western
areas.
</P>
<P>
This has pushed the total investment to Shenyang's transport
construction to nearly 1.3 billion by the HK group company, the
largest amount of overseas investment the city has attracted.
</P>
<P>
Local sources report that the city's running water supply
company has also signed a contract with the Hong Kong business
tycoon to invest 200 million yuan each in a water supply project.
</P>
<P>
</P>
