<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Corporate Bonds Appealing to Qinghai Individual Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Corporate bonds have proven
attractive to individual investors in northwest China's Qinghai
Province, as a recent bond offer has shown.
</P>
<P>
Some 3.5 million yuan (about 420,000 US dollars) in power
sector bonds were sold in the first two days of a 40-million-yuan
bond offer on May 10.
</P>
<P>
The bond issue was approved by the provincial planning
commission and the provincial branch of the central bank. They
have an annual interest rate of 10.2 percent, which is higher than
that of savings deposits or similar treasury bonds.
</P>
<P>
Funds from the issue will be used to finance the Lijiaxia
Hydroelectric Power Station and an expansion project on the
Qinghai Qiaotou Power Plant.
</P>
<P>
Relatively underdeveloped Qinghai is rich in power resources
but suffers from a shortage of funds.
</P>
<P>
Corporate bonds are still issued on a small scale, but have
become appealing to individual Chinese after two interest cuts
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
