<HEADLINE> Colombian President Meets Chinese Vice-Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFI DE BOGOTA, May 14 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing said here today there are great
potentialities in the development of Sino-Colombian cooperation,
in all ways.
</P>
<P>
Li, who arrived here Tuesday on a two-day visit, told
Colombian President Ernesto Samper that China and Colombia, which
are both developing countries, enjoy good prospects in the
development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Samper said the Colombian government attached great importance
to friendly cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
He said Colombia expects cooperation with China in the building
of infrastructure, including railways, roads and bridges, and the
production and refining of oil and coal.
</P>
<P>
Li left here today for Chile, the fourth leg of his Latin
American tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
