<HEADLINE> Becker Enters Third Round in Rome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 14 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker set up a third round
match against Goran Ivanisevic at the Italian Open when he edged
Cedric Pioline of France 6-4, 7-5 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Becker, the German 12th seed, played a solid game and never
looked in danger of losing the second round tie. His superior
racquet skills more than compensated for the unforced errors he
made.
</P>
<P>
Pioline had been his country's last man in the tournament after
Spain's Alex Corretja had downed Arnaud Boetsch 6-2, 6-3 and
Chilean seventh seed Marcelo Rios hammered Fabrice Santoro 6-2,
6-2. 
</P>
