<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said in Beijing yesterday that
adopting "one country, two systems," "the principle of Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong" and a high degree of autonomy towards
Hong Kong is China's long-term state policy.
</P>
<P>
This will not only benefit the six million Hong Kong
compatriots, but also conform to the interests of the whole
country, said Jiang during a meeting with a delegation from the
Hong Kong-based Guangdong Societies' Committee to greet Hong
Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji met with Alan Greenspan, chairman of
the Board of Governors of the US Federal Reserve System, and his
party in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Zhu briefed the US visitors on China's economic development
and reform of the state-owned enterprises, saying that he hoped
that the central banks of the two countries would increase
exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said yesterday
that China attaches great importance to its relations with
Malaysia, and is ready to build a good-neighborly relationship of
mutual trust and cooperation with Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remark in talks with visiting Malaysian Foreign
Minister Datuk Abdullah Bin Haji Badawi in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin said in Beijing yesterday that the
fight against desertification, environmental protection, economic
development and poverty elimination are tough and urgent tasks
facing all Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark during a meeting with participants to the
Asian Ministerial Conference on the Implementation of the UN
Convention on Combating Desertification (UNCCD), co-organized by
the Chinese government and the UNCCD temporary secretariat.
</P>
<P>
-- Recent years have seen smooth growth of relations between
China and Vietnam, and frequent exchanges of high-level visits,
said Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) during a
meeting with Le Quang Dao, president of the Central Committee of
the Vietnam Fatherland Front, and his party in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A new concept of family doctors who treat patients in their
homes and neighborhoods has been launched in some of China's
major cities.
</P>
<P>
-- The two sides of the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLP)
have reached agreement on China dispatching two more advance
parties of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) garrison to Hong
Kong, a spokesman for the Chinese side said here yesterday.
</P>
</TEXT>
