<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Copper Prices in China not Volatile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Copper prices in China's market
will follow fluctuations in the international market this month
with only marginal prices changes, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Lower domestic prices and higher international prices will be
maintained until the demand for copper in the domestic market
surges, according to a report from Antaike Information Corp under
the China National Nonferrous Metals Industry Corp (CNNC).
</P>
<P>
China produced 211,400 tons of refined copper in the first
quarter of this year, up 9.38 percent over the corresponding
period last year, according to CNNC.
</P>
<P>
China imported 13,012 tons of refined cooper during the
January-March period, a reduction of 8.35 percent from the same
period last year, according to the customs records.
</P>
<P>
Cooper exports during the period stood at 24,061 tons, 305
percent higher than the first quarter of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the drop in copper imports and the rises
in exports to the price differentials between the international
and China's market.
</P>
<P>
A further review of the imports and exports of the copper shows
that most imported copper is roughly processed while exported
copper is thoroughly processed, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
