<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Foreign Cooperation in Ostrich Breeding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 15 (Xinhua) -- China welcomes foreign
cooperation in introducing ostrich industry to China, said Ma
Shan, managing director of the China Association for Ostrich
Breeding.
</P>
<P>
Ma said China has built more than 400 ostrich farms and keeps
at present 70,000 ostriches. and ostrich breeding bases have been
built up in Guangdong, Liaoning and Shandong provinces.
</P>
<P>
Ostrich raising has witnessed a rapid growth in the world as the
feather, meat, egg, hair and bone of the ostriches are all of high
economic value .
</P>
<P>
China began its ostrich raising five years ago and has
introduced breeding ostriches from African, European and American
countries, and Australia.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China spent 35 million US dollars to import breeding
ostriches.
</P>
<P>
Ma said, most of Chinese regions are situated for ostrich
breeding and China is drawing up long-range plans for the
development of ostrich breeding so as to keep more than one
million ostriches by the end of the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
