<DOCNO> XIE19970515.0315 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IBF Strips Pastrana of His Junior Flyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 14 (Xinhua) -- The International Boxing
Federation Wednesday stripped Mauricio Pastrana of his junior
flyweight title for failing to attend a weigh-in for a May 10
title defense.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian was scheduled to fight Manuel Herrara in Coconut
Grove, Florida, last Saturday, but instead of turning up for
Friday's weigh-in, Pastrana sent word through a representative
that he was ill.
</P>
<P>
IBF President Bob Lee said in a news release in East Orange,
New Jersey, that the Florida Commission sent a doctor to
Pastrana's room to examine the champion and the doctor declared
him fit to fight, despite Pastrana's complaints of pain in his
testicles.
</P>
<P>
IBF rules state that a fighter must appear at a weigh-in for a
title bout unless he notifies the sanctioning body with a doctor's
certificate that he is unable to fight. When Pastrana declined to
appear, he effectively forfeited his title, the IBF said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
