<DOCNO> XIE19970515.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qingdao Keeps Up Foreign Trade Growth Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, May 15 (Xinhua) -- Imports and exports in Qingdao, a
coastal city in east China's Shandong Province, totalled 1.5
billion US dollars in the first four months of this year, up 70
percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Of that amount, exports came to one billion US dollars, a 30
percent rise, and import increased markedly to 510 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The export of machinery and electronic products, major export
commodity of Qingdao, rose by 1.2 percentage points to 160 million
US dollars. The export of primary products dropped by 0.9
percentage point, to 90 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises played a big role, with exports
increasing by 55 percent.
</P>
<P>
The processing industry achieved an export volume of 700 million US
dollars in the first four months, accounting for 68 percent of the
city's total exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
