<DOCNO> XIE19970515.0322 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Flirts 7,300 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 14 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks ended barely
higher today, sliding into the close after rallying with the bond
market.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average, which rose by as much as 77
points in the morning, gained just 11.95 points to 7,286.16. It is
now less than 7 points shy of Monday's record high.
</P>
<P>
The New York Stock Exchange composite index rose 1.63 to
435.60, barely topping Monday's record close at 435.57. But the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 2.92 to 836.05, about 1.5
points below Monday's record.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 1.96 to 1,335.55, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 2.37 to 581.97.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by nearly a 3-to-2 margin on
the NYSE, where volume totaled 498.75 million shares as against
489.71 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The bond market rallied after the Labor Department reported
that wholesale prices paid to farms, factories and other producers
fell 0.6 percent in April, the largest drop in nearly four years
and the fourth straight decline.
</P>
<P>
The yield on the 30-year Treasury bond fell to 6.88 percent,
down from 6.92 percent late Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
